DataElement.preferredName: Clinical Study Site Institutional Review Board Approval Date Start Date java.util.Date
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A healthcare organization, a facility, a healthcare provider, or a part or a constituent of any of the above entities directly involved in conducting a particular clinical study._A date on which the Institutional Review Board (IRB) approved a clinical study protocol for execution at the particular institution or site. If the study receives full unconditional approval at a convened meeting, the date of IRB approval is the date of this convened meeting. If at the convened IRB meeting the study is approved subject to modifications, the date of IRB approval is the date when the requested changes are verified.:The calendar date on which something is to start or did start._Generic value domain for a java datatype that represents a specific instant in time, with millisecond precision.
